Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the functional decomposition of polynomials, which is a topic in pure and computer algebra. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an efficient algorithm to compute the rational Jordan form of the Frobenius automorphism on the root space of the polynomial. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is a possibility as the paper may involve the development of software tools for computing the rational Jordan form and counting the number of invariant subspaces. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper mentions the Frobenius automorphism, which is a concept used in game theory. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper deals with the field size and exponent of the polynomial, which are numerical quantities.
